President Obama announced his intent to nominate Barbara J. Bennett as Chief Financial Officer of the Environmental Protection Agency and Michael Punke as Deputy Trade Representative in Geneva. Bennett has extensive experience as a global business executive, previously serving as the CFO of Discovery Communications. Punke has worked in international trade law and policy for two decades, including serving as Senior Policy Advisor at the Office of the United States Trade Representative. President Obama also announced that Thomas Paul D'Agostino will continue serving as Under Secretary for Nuclear Security at the Department of Energy and Administrator for Nuclear Security of the National Nuclear Security Administration. D'Agostino has been in this role since August 2007 and is responsible for the safe and reliable maintenance of nuclear weapons for the U.S. military.